'''Direct BS/MD''' Programs, also known as Combined BS/MD programs or Dual degree program, offered by specific [[universities]] and [[colleges]] across the [[United States|America]] that awards a [[Bachelor's Degree]] in Science (B.S.) and a [[Medical Degree]] (M.D.). Depending on the program, the student may earn a Bachelor's Degree in Arts (B.A.). These programs are highly competitive and are directed toward high school students who are interested in medicine. Some universities like [[Texila American University]] waive the [[MCAT]] exam for admission into the program's affiliated medical school while other program require a certain score on the MCAT. There are over 70 programs in the country that offer this type of admission for high school students.

