{{For|the similarly titled journal|American Journal of Translational Research}} {{Infobox journal | title = Translational Research | cover = [[File:Translational Research journal cover.jpg|200px]] | caption = | former_name = The Journal of Laboratory and Clinical Medicine<!-- or |former_names= --> | abbreviation = Transl. Res. | discipline = [[Translational research]] | editor = [[Jeffrey Laurence]]<!-- or |editors= --> | publisher = [[Mosby (imprint)|Mosby]] | country = | history = 1915-present | frequency = Monthly | openaccess = | license = | impact = 5.03 | impact-year = 2014 | ISSNlabel = | ISSN = 1931-5244 | eISSN = 1878-1810 | CODEN = JLCMAK | JSTOR = | LCCN = 2006212275 | OCLC = 66901338 | website = http://www.translationalres.com/ | link1 = http://www.translationalres.com/current | link1-name = Online access | link2 = http://www.translationalres.com/issues | link2-name = Online archive | link3 = http://www.journals.elsevier.com/translational-research-the-journal-of-laboratory-and-clinical-medicine/ | link3-name = Journal page on publisher's website | boxwidth = }} '''''Translational Research: The Journal of Laboratory and Clinical Medicine''''' is a monthly [[peer-reviewed]] [[medical journal]] covering [[translational research]]. It was established in 1915 as '''''The Journal of Laboratory and Clinical Medicine''''' obtaining its current title in 2006. [[Jeffrey Laurence]] ([[Weill Cornell Medical College]]) has been [[editor-in-chief]] since 2006.<ref name="Laurence2006">{{cite journal |last1= Laurence |first1= J |year= 2006 |title= Translating transitional research |url= http://www.translationalres.com/article/S0022-2143%2806%2900140-5/fulltext |volume= 148 |issue= 1 |pages= 1–3 |journal= Translational Research |doi= 10.1016/j.lab.2006.04.003 |pmid= 16887490}}</ref> He was preceded by Dale Hammerschmidt.<ref name="Laurence2006"/> It is the official journal of the [[Central Society for Clinical and Translational Research]]. It is published by [[Mosby (imprint)|Mosby]].
==Abstracting and indexing== The journal is abstracted and indexed in: {{columns-list|colwidth=30em| *[[Academic OneFile]]<ref name=UWEB/> *[[BIOSIS Previews]]<ref name=ISI/> *[[CAB Abstracts]]<ref name=UWEB/> *[[CINAHL]]<ref name=CINAHL>{{cite web |url=http://www.ebscohost.com/titleLists/ccf-coverage.htm |title=CINAHL Complete Database Coverage List |publisher=[[EBSCO Information Services]] |work=[[CINAHL]] |accessdate=2014-12-27}}</ref> *[[Current Contents]]/Clinical Medicine<ref name=ISI/> *Current Contents/Life Sciences<ref name=ISI/> *[[Elsevier BIOBASE]]<ref name=UWEB>{{cite web |title= ''Translational Research'' |url= http://www.ulrichsweb.serialssolutions.com/title/1419617004378/48142 |work= [[Ulrichsweb]] |publisher= [[ProQuest]] |accessdate=2014-12-26 |subscription= yes}}</ref> *[[Embase]]<ref name=UWEB/> *[[GeoRef]]<ref name=UWEB/> *[[Global Health]]<ref name=UWEB/> *[[Index Medicus]]/[[MEDLINE]]/[[PubMed]]<ref name=MEDLINE>{{cite web |url= https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/nlmcatalog/101280339 |title= ''Translational Research: The Journal of Laboratory and Clinical Medicine'' |work= [[United States National Library of Medicine|NLM]] Catalog |publisher= [[National Center for Biotechnology Information]] |accessdate= }}</ref> * [[Science Citation Index]]<ref name=ISI>{{cite web |url= http://ip-science.thomsonreuters.com/mjl/ |title= Master Journal List |publisher= [[Thomson Reuters]] |work= Intellectual Property & Science |accessdate= }}</ref> *[[Scopus]]<ref name=UWEB/> *[[Tropical Diseases Bulletin]]<ref name=UWEB/> }}
According to the ''[[Journal Citation Reports]]'', the journal has a 2014 [[impact factor]] of 5.03, ranking it second out of 30 journals in the category "Medical Laboratory Technology",<ref name=WoS2>{{cite book |year=2015 |chapter=Journals Ranked by Impact: Medical Laboratory Technology |title=2014 Journal Citation Reports |publisher=[[Thomson Reuters]] |edition=Science |series=[[Web of Science]]}}</ref> 17th out of 153 journals in the category "Medicine, General & Internal"<ref name=WoS3>{{cite book |year=2015 |chapter=Journals Ranked by Impact: Medicine, General & Internal |title=2014 Journal Citation Reports |publisher=Thomson Reuters |edition=Science |series=Web of Science}}</ref> and 17th out of 123 journals in the category "Medicine, Research & Experimental"<ref name=WoS4>{{cite book |year=2015 |chapter=Journals Ranked by Impact: Medicine, Research & Experimental |title=2014 Journal Citation Reports |publisher=Thomson Reuters |edition=Science |series=Web of Science}}</ref>
